

TASK: 2, How to mount EFS to EC2 Instance:
 Ref: 
  - https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/wt1-test.html

 Step 3.3: Mount the file system on your EC2 instance and test
  - cd /
  - mkdir /efs
  - EFS --> Network --> click on attach --> Using the NFS Clinet --> copy the cmd & paste it on cmd
    Ex:
    - sudo mount -t nfs -o nfsvers=4.1,rsize=1048576,wsize=1048576,hard,timeo=600,retrans=2,noresvport <mount-target-DNS>:/  /efs  
  - df -h
  - cd /efs/
  - ls
